<DOC><DOCNO> AP890831-0073 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-31-89 1008EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--BuildingPlunge     08-31 0159</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Building Plunge,0163</SECOND><HEAD>Window Washer Dies in High-Rise Plunge</HEAD><DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two window washers cleaning a high-risebuilding plunged 10 stories today when their platform collapsed. Oneof the workers died, and two people walking near the building wereinjured, police said.   Sydney police Sgt. Doug Townsend said the platform broke freefrom its fastenings above a crowded mall.   One worker fell 132 feet to his death while the other ``rode''the platform as it slid down a cable to the second floor, then fellto the ground, he said.   The condition of the surviving window washer was not immediatelyknown, but witnesses said he was badly cut on his face, hands andchest.   ``There were things strewn everywhere and people were justdistraught,'' Townsend said.   The accident occurred while downtown Martin Place was crowdedwith lunchtime shoppers. At least two people on the ground wereinjured, and four children were treated for shock, police said.</TEXT></DOC>